@lsm5 Yes, the RISE runners need the [RISE RISC-V Runners GitHub App](https://github.com/apps/rise-risc-v-runners) installed on the containers org. It requires Actions read/write permissions to register runners.

@luhenry could you help get the RISE runner app set up for the containers/podman org? The maintainers are ready to try a non-blocking riscv64 CI build.

In the meantime, the workflow is validated on my fork: https://github.com/gounthar/podman/actions/runs/23318754735
